1. Create a file with .txt extension (/home/demo.txt). 
Change the permission set if that file, so that any user can read it, the group can read/write & owner can read/write/execute it.

jananirv@LAPTOP-KLQNB7V6:~$ pwd
/home/jananirv

jananirv@LAPTOP-KLQNB7V6:~$ sudo touch /home/demo.txt

jananirv@LAPTOP-KLQNB7V6:~$ ls -ltr /home/demo.txt
-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 0 Aug 17 15:43 /home/demo.txt

jananirv@LAPTOP-KLQNB7V6:~$ sudo chmod 467 /home/demo.txt

jananirv@LAPTOP-KLQNB7V6:~$ ls -ltr /home/demo.txt
-r--rw-rwx 1 root root 0 Aug 17 15:43 /home/demo.txt
jananirv@LAPTOP-KLQNB7V6:~$

